1
00:00:14,734 --> 00:00:20,172
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:21,006 --> 00:00:28,913
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,981 --> 00:00:34,351
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:38,481
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,725 --> 00:00:44,628
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,364 --> 00:00:52,270
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,672 --> 00:00:57,164
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,243 --> 00:01:04,206
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,283 --> 00:01:11,348
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,424 --> 00:01:18,091
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,564 --> 00:01:28,064
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:31,321 --> 00:01:33,482
Fire Style! Fire Ball Jutsu!

13
00:01:39,529 --> 00:01:41,724
<i>Wh-What is that Jutsu?!</i>

14
00:01:47,304 --> 00:01:48,236
Damn it!

15
00:01:50,974 --> 00:01:51,906
Chidori: One Thousand Birds!

16
00:01:54,544 --> 00:01:55,909
I'll win no matter what!

17
00:01:56,046 --> 00:01:57,946
Don't flatter yourself!

18
00:02:01,785 --> 00:02:03,013
Stop it!

19
00:02:08,825 --> 00:02:10,315
<i>Bitter Rivals and Broken Bonds</i>

20
00:02:26,243 --> 00:02:28,336
It's a tranquil village as always...

21
00:02:28,845 --> 00:02:30,574
The security sucks.

22
00:02:31,014 --> 00:02:31,776
Humph!

23
00:02:31,848 --> 00:02:37,115
We should just massacre everybody
in such a seedy village.

24
00:02:37,521 --> 00:02:39,113
Calm down, Sakon.

25
00:02:39,589 --> 00:02:41,921
We haven't come here to fight.

26
00:02:42,025 --> 00:02:44,016
Shut up, you chicken.

27
00:02:44,227 --> 00:02:45,353
If you're scared,

28
00:02:45,428 --> 00:02:47,089
you should just go home
and go to bed already.

29
00:02:47,364 --> 00:02:49,832
I'm telling you to calm down, Tayuya.

30
00:02:50,634 --> 00:02:53,194
You understand what
our job is this time, right?

31
00:02:53,904 --> 00:02:56,896
Let's go.
We escort our special guest.

32
00:03:05,048 --> 00:03:07,175
Stop it!

33
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:11,445
<i>Damn.</i>

34
00:03:12,188 --> 00:03:13,553
<i>I can't stop completely.</i>

35
00:03:26,836 --> 00:03:27,894
<i>Kakashi Sensei?</i>

36
00:03:29,539 --> 00:03:31,370
<i>Naruto... That thing you just did was...</i>

37
00:03:40,317 --> 00:03:42,615
What're you guys doing
up on top of the hospital?

38
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:47,115
You went a bit too far
for just a fight, you two.

39
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:58,728
<i>That Jutsu earlier, no mistake.</i>

40
00:03:59,536 --> 00:04:01,231
<i>It's the Rasengan.</i>

41
00:04:06,509 --> 00:04:07,533
<i>What's going on?</i>

42
00:04:07,844 --> 00:04:10,142
<i>How can Naruto use that Jutsu...?</i>

43
00:04:23,326 --> 00:04:26,318
Were you going to kill Naruto, Sasuke?

44
00:04:29,099 --> 00:04:31,829
What're you doing giving yourself over
to a sense of superiority?

45
00:04:35,271 --> 00:04:38,001
The size of the Chidori there
wasn't one to be aimed

46
00:04:38,074 --> 00:04:40,167
at a comrade of the same village.

47
00:04:46,149 --> 00:04:48,879
Why such infantile behavior...?

48
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,686
<i>Sure enough, a reunion with Itachi...</i>

49
00:05:07,404 --> 00:05:08,462
Sasuke.

50
00:05:27,023 --> 00:05:27,955
<i>Damn it!</i>

51
00:05:32,295 --> 00:05:33,353
<i>Naruto...</i>

52
00:05:34,064 --> 00:05:36,089
<i>How far will you go...?</i>

53
00:06:28,952 --> 00:06:30,419
Kakashi Sensei...

54
00:06:38,695 --> 00:06:40,856
<i>Whatever happened to teamwork?</i>

55
00:06:42,298 --> 00:06:45,426
Was it you...
who taught him that technique?

56
00:06:46,669 --> 00:06:51,368
I think Naruto is still too young
to be handling that Jutsu.

57
00:06:55,311 --> 00:06:57,575
He could've killed Sasuke
had something gone wrong...

58
00:06:59,282 --> 00:07:02,376
Even if it's a means of resisting
the Akatsuki,

59
00:07:02,452 --> 00:07:04,682
to think you would teach Naruto
that Jutsu...

60
00:07:05,822 --> 00:07:07,790
Right back at you...

61
00:07:08,858 --> 00:07:11,691
That Chidori was also considerably hairy.

62
00:07:12,061 --> 00:07:14,655
But I didn't think he was
the kind of kid

63
00:07:14,731 --> 00:07:18,565
who'd fire that Jutsu at his comrade.

64
00:07:19,869 --> 00:07:23,703
Or is it that there's something quite
complicated between him and that kid?

65
00:07:25,141 --> 00:07:27,234
Well, all sorts.

66
00:07:27,877 --> 00:07:29,037
All sorts?

67
00:07:29,612 --> 00:07:31,876
Quite simply, it's a relationship

68
00:07:31,948 --> 00:07:34,542
like the one between you
and Orochimaru in the past.

69
00:07:38,588 --> 00:07:39,577
I see.

70
00:07:41,157 --> 00:07:45,025
To him, Sasuke is a comrade
and a rival at the same time...

71
00:07:45,762 --> 00:07:49,528
Well, someone he considers
an equal.

72
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:54,464
Most likely, he couldn't take
Sasuke's cheap provocation.

73
00:07:55,572 --> 00:07:58,405
He's been chasing him...

74
00:07:59,442 --> 00:08:01,376
Chasing him since the Academy days.

75
00:08:01,911 --> 00:08:03,572
<i>Are you hurt...</i>

76
00:08:05,014 --> 00:08:06,208
<i>Scaredy Cat?</i>

77
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:11,517
<i>Sasuke!</i>

78
00:08:16,693 --> 00:08:18,752
<i>I won't lose to you!</i>

79
00:08:20,330 --> 00:08:23,891
For him, it's neither you
nor me now...

80
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:26,062
More than anyone...

81
00:08:26,169 --> 00:08:29,764
he wants to be recognized by Sasuke.

82
00:08:32,108 --> 00:08:33,700
On the other side of the coin...

83
00:08:33,776 --> 00:08:38,179
Sasuke feels the speed of Naruto's growth
at close range and feels inferior.

84
00:08:38,815 --> 00:08:43,445
To the extent that he thinks
he himself isn't growing at all.

85
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,317
<i>Scaredy Cat?</i>

86
00:08:45,455 --> 00:08:47,821
<i>Multi Shadow Clone Jutsu!</i>

87
00:08:48,258 --> 00:08:49,919
<i>Summoning Jutsu!</i>

88
00:08:55,798 --> 00:08:58,460
Naruto has gotten strong...

89
00:08:59,202 --> 00:09:00,669
And Sasuke...

90
00:09:01,838 --> 00:09:05,706
<i>I'm going to kill a certain man,</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

91
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:08,272
Revenge, huh?

92
00:09:09,379 --> 00:09:12,473
I wonder if Itachi
is frustrating that kid.

93
00:09:13,917 --> 00:09:16,579
So Sasuke doesn't want
to acknowledge Naruto.

94
00:09:16,853 --> 00:09:18,377
If he acknowledges him,

95
00:09:18,655 --> 00:09:21,783
he just might deny himself
up to this point...

96
00:09:22,659 --> 00:09:25,651
Rivalry is a difficult thing

97
00:09:26,562 --> 00:09:29,030
It's not a very good trend...

98
00:09:29,866 --> 00:09:32,232
Maybe I'll do some scolding.

99
00:09:32,769 --> 00:09:34,862
Then I leave Naruto to you.

100
00:09:35,438 --> 00:09:39,033
Well, I have a mission.
And there's the Chidori thing, too...

101
00:09:42,612 --> 00:09:43,408
Sakura.

102
00:09:44,814 --> 00:09:48,614
It's okay. Things can go back to the way
they were in the old days again.

103
00:09:49,819 --> 00:09:50,649
Cheer up.

104
00:09:52,255 --> 00:09:53,222
See ya.

105
00:10:01,731 --> 00:10:03,892
<i>Thanks, Kakashi Sensei.</i>

106
00:10:07,804 --> 00:10:08,793
Naruto...

107
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,304
Sakura.

108
00:10:15,945 --> 00:10:17,936
Don't interfere with us!

109
00:10:47,343 --> 00:10:49,470
<i>You are weak.</i>

110
00:10:50,213 --> 00:10:51,874
<i>Why are you weak?</i>

111
00:10:53,082 --> 00:10:55,141
<i>It's because you don't have enough...</i>

112
00:10:55,318 --> 00:10:56,546
<i>...hate.</i>

113
00:10:58,021 --> 00:10:59,716
<i>What've I been doing...</i>

114
00:11:01,657 --> 00:11:03,284
<i>up until now?</i>

115
00:11:15,338 --> 00:11:16,737
He got a nice look in those eyes.

116
00:11:32,122 --> 00:11:33,589
Shall we go soon?

117
00:12:39,489 --> 00:12:40,820
What do you think you're doing?

118
00:12:41,325 --> 00:12:44,089
If I don't do this,
you'll run away, right?

119
00:12:44,294 --> 00:12:47,457
You're not the type
to listen quietly to lectures.

120
00:12:49,966 --> 00:12:52,799
As I recall,
that's Kakashi the Copy Ninja.

121
00:12:56,139 --> 00:12:59,700
Sasuke... Forget about something
like revenge.

122
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:00,899
What?

123
00:13:02,045 --> 00:13:06,311
Well, in this business
I've seen a stink of guys like you.

124
00:13:07,417 --> 00:13:10,909
But the final days of those who speak
of revenge are never good.

125
00:13:12,389 --> 00:13:13,651
They're tragic.

126
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:21,256
You'll only hurt yourself and
agonize more than now.

127
00:13:22,132 --> 00:13:26,398
Even if you succeed in revenge,
all that will remain is emptiness.

128
00:13:26,503 --> 00:13:27,470
Shut up!

129
00:13:27,738 --> 00:13:29,228
What do you know?

130
00:13:29,606 --> 00:13:32,507
Don't talk to me as if you know!

131
00:13:32,576 --> 00:13:34,942
Well, calm down...

132
00:13:35,512 --> 00:13:37,036
If you like,

133
00:13:37,114 --> 00:13:40,379
shall I go and kill the person
most important to you?

134
00:13:40,851 --> 00:13:43,752
You'll be able to realize just
how far off you are

135
00:13:43,820 --> 00:13:45,185
on what you just said.

136
00:13:45,622 --> 00:13:48,614
Well, I wouldn't mind if you'd do that.

137
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:52,651
Unfortunately, I don't even have
one person like that.

138
00:13:54,631 --> 00:13:57,293
Everyone's already been killed.

139
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:02,229
I've lived longer than you have...

140
00:14:03,106 --> 00:14:04,266
The times were not good.

141
00:14:05,675 --> 00:14:09,372
I know all too well
the agony of losing something.

142
00:14:13,216 --> 00:14:16,242
Well, both you and I
aren't the lucky ones...

143
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,382
That's for darned sure.

144
00:14:19,689 --> 00:14:22,021
But we're not the worst, either.

145
00:14:23,326 --> 00:14:24,987
You and I,

146
00:14:25,061 --> 00:14:27,962
we both have already found
dear comrades, haven't we?

147
00:14:34,871 --> 00:14:37,101
It's because I have lost
that I understand.

148
00:14:37,974 --> 00:14:39,373
The Chidori is a power...

149
00:14:39,443 --> 00:14:42,776
I gave to you because
you now have something important.

150
00:14:44,281 --> 00:14:46,181
You should know that
it's not a power

151
00:14:46,249 --> 00:14:48,809
to be used on your comrade
or to use for revenge,

152
00:14:48,885 --> 00:14:52,685
and I'm sure you know
what it should be used for.

153
00:14:53,490 --> 00:14:58,427
Think hard about whether or not
what I'm saying is wrong.

154
00:15:09,206 --> 00:15:12,437
It'll be tricky with a Shinobi
of that level hanging around.

155
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,841
So let's wait a bit.

156
00:15:15,378 --> 00:15:20,213
Maybe jerks like you'd be no good.
But I could do it.

157
00:15:20,417 --> 00:15:25,184
I wonder. "Two"
should be ample to rip him apart.

158
00:15:25,589 --> 00:15:28,854
Don't be butting in all the time,
you clod.

159
00:15:30,060 --> 00:15:33,029
Tayuya, women shouldn't
use words like that too...

160
00:15:33,096 --> 00:15:34,461
Shut up, fatso.

161
00:16:45,235 --> 00:16:46,327
- <i>More, please!</i>
- <i>More, please!</i>

162
00:16:55,712 --> 00:16:56,576
<i>Wanna head back?</i>

163
00:16:57,013 --> 00:16:57,980
<i>Sure!</i>

164
00:16:59,616 --> 00:17:02,847
<i>We both made it</i>
<i>to the top of the tree.</i>

165
00:17:24,174 --> 00:17:25,072
Sakura.

166
00:17:26,242 --> 00:17:28,039
I have a something to talk
to you about.

167
00:17:28,478 --> 00:17:31,072
I'll go out on a date with you,
so come along.

168
00:17:52,502 --> 00:17:53,730
Damn it...

169
00:17:57,007 --> 00:17:58,167
Damn it!

170
00:18:26,970 --> 00:18:30,565
<i>The Curse Mark left by Orochimaru</i>
<i>during the Chunin Exam...</i>

171
00:18:39,549 --> 00:18:42,950
<i>Kakashi Sensei said</i>
<i>it was okay now, but...</i>

172
00:18:59,536 --> 00:19:00,662
Master Orochimaru.

173
00:19:01,504 --> 00:19:05,065
You didn't need to send out
all four members, did you?

174
00:19:06,076 --> 00:19:11,810
It seems those kids are all interested
in Sasuke to whom I've taken a liking.

175
00:19:12,515 --> 00:19:14,983
To see what extent his power is...

176
00:19:15,285 --> 00:19:17,253
A contest of strength or whatever,

177
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:20,483
at this point Sasuke would be
no match for them.

178
00:19:24,861 --> 00:19:30,163
That is precisely why... he will come to me
in search of power.

179
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:38,871
Who're you guys?

180
00:19:39,709 --> 00:19:43,736
I'm Kidomaru, the East Gate
of the Sound Ninja Four.

181
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:46,348
I'm Sakon,
the West Gate of the same.

182
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:49,111
I'm Jirobo,
the South Gate of the same.

183
00:19:49,919 --> 00:19:51,978
I'm Tayuya,
the North Gate of the same.

184
00:20:54,617 --> 00:20:56,710
I'm in a bad mood now...

185
00:20:57,887 --> 00:20:59,787
If you wanna continue to fight her,

186
00:20:59,989 --> 00:21:01,456
I won't go easy on you!

187
00:21:12,502 --> 00:21:19,601
<i>Once in a long while, once in a while</i>

188
00:21:19,742 --> 00:21:25,271
<i>The remnants of a person</i>
<i>broken by dreams</i>

189
00:21:25,448 --> 00:21:30,511
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

190
00:21:33,823 --> 00:21:40,820
<i>Clinging to the Divine,</i>
<i>clinging to Buddha</i>

191
00:21:40,897 --> 00:21:46,426
<i>The remnants of a person crying</i>

192
00:21:46,836 --> 00:21:50,397
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

193
00:21:52,075 --> 00:21:55,135
<i>Rendezvous with a happy dance circle</i>

194
00:21:55,211 --> 00:21:59,011
<i>This is my victory pose, round and around</i>
<i>(round around)</i>

195
00:21:59,349 --> 00:22:02,284
<i>Shake shake shake</i>
<i>Let's look</i>

196
00:22:02,352 --> 00:22:06,482
<i>With a bye bye rhythm that never ends</i>

197
00:22:15,665 --> 00:22:20,762
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

198
00:22:22,705 --> 00:22:25,970
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

199
00:22:26,376 --> 00:22:29,573
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

200
00:22:29,846 --> 00:22:33,839
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

201
00:22:37,553 --> 00:22:39,612
A date, a date!

202
00:22:39,689 --> 00:22:41,122
What do you want to eat, Sakura?

203
00:22:41,190 --> 00:22:41,884
Anything's fine.

204
00:22:41,958 --> 00:22:45,018
At any rate,
Kakashi Sensei's over the top.

205
00:22:45,228 --> 00:22:47,788
I just wanted to fight
Sasuke a little.

206
00:22:47,997 --> 00:22:50,932
But if Kakashi Sensei hadn't stopped it,
right about now...

207
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,868
Of course, which of us was stronger
would be settled, believe it.

208
00:22:55,104 --> 00:22:56,662
Listen, Naruto...

209
00:22:57,206 --> 00:22:59,106
Next time:
"An Invitation from the Sound"

210
00:22:59,676 --> 00:23:01,974
I feel uneasy...
